      <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
        <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
        <p>MR. SPEAKER : Order, please. We'll now proceed with the daily routine.</p>
      </speech>
      <debateSection>
        <heading>TABLING REPORTS, REGULATIONS AND OTHER PAPERS</heading>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : The honourable Government House Leader.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#7577a3e3-867e-4d2e-a20f-cf0febdf9d97">
          <from>HON. MICHEL SAMSON</from>
          <p>HON. MICHEL SAMSON : M. le Pr&#xE9;sident, j'ai le plaisir de pr&#xE9;senter le Rapport d'&#xE9;tape 2013 sur les Services en fran&#xE7;ais offerts par le gouvernement de la Nouvelle-&#xC9;cosse.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : The report is tabled.</p>
        </speech>
      </debateSection>
      <debateSection>
        <heading>STATEMENTS BY MINISTERS</heading>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : The honourable Minister of Labour and Advanced Education.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#6d07f2ae-9d4e-4ecf-8c75-26d9d9438690">
          <from>HON. KELLY REGAN</from>
          <p>HON. KELLY REGAN : Mr. Speaker, I rise today to recognize April 28th as the National Day of Mourning. Every year we join together on this day to pay tribute to the workers who have been killed, injured, or suffered illness because of workplace hazards or incidents.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : The honourable member for Pictou Centre.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#1e9f2e89-d643-4114-bd3d-f08b90917121">
          <from>HON. PAT DUNN</from>
          <p>HON. PAT DUNN : Mr. Speaker, I want to thank the minister for providing a copy of her remarks earlier today.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : The honourable Leader of the New Democratic Party.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#40342c81-d15f-4412-9e39-be7ba9a478a9">
          <from>HON. MAUREEN MACDONALD</from>
          <p>HON. MAUREEN MACDONALD : Mr. Speaker, I want to, first, thank the minister for providing a copy of her remarks in advance. Today, as we all know, is the National Day of Mourning, a day to remember those who have gone to work in the morning and not come home at night. Sadly, in our province there were 34 workplace fatalities since this time last year.</p>
        </speech>
      </debateSection>
      <debateSection>
